info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Statement issued November 16 at 6:05AM EST until November 17 at 5:00AM EST by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD STATEMENT IN EFFECT THROUGH LATE TONIGHT... ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IS CANCELLED... * WHAT...Minor saltwater flooding. * WHERE...Florida Keys. * WHEN...During the hours of higher high tide. * IMPACTS...Minor saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is likely. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
